
Overview of verb sift

The verb sift has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) sift -- (move as if through a sieve; "The soldiers sifted through the woods")
2. (1) sift, sieve, strain -- (separate by passing through a sieve or other straining device to separate out coarser elements; "sift the flour")
3. sieve, sift -- (check and sort carefully; "sift the information")
4. sieve, sift -- (distinguish and separate out; "sift through the job candidates")
